cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use klue in published work, please cite both the methodology paper and the software."
title: "klue: Hybrid Machine Learning and Random-Utility Workflow for Latent Class Multinomial Logit Model Specification"
abstract: "An R package implementing the three-step workflow from Frings (2026) for specifying latent class multinomial logit (LCMNL) models: cluster-based initialisation of the maximum-likelihood multi-start, LCMNL estimation across class counts, and MMNL benchmarking with BIC, AIC, ICL, and classification-entropy diagnostics."
type: software
authors:
